The Plateau State Police Command, on Sunday confirmed that four men lost their lives at a mining site by some yet-to-be-identified gunmen. The four men were reportedly killed on a Saturday evening. The Command's spokesperson, Ubah Ogaba, disclosed this in on SundayOgaba said, “Four men who went to a mining site at Mai Farin Mota were shot dead by yet to be identified gunmen. The scene was visited by the police and has been beefed up with security.”